T1  - Intertemporal Equilibrium and the Transfer Paradox
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297450
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 1
SP  - 147
EP  - 156
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The transfer paradox may occur in a world with only two countries at a dynamically stable intertemporal competitive equilibrium. In a framework of overlapping generations with production and investment, a transfer of income may immiserize the recipient while enriching the donor. Away from the golden rule, a transfer may result in a Pareto improvement.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297450
ER  - 



