TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bonanno, Giacomo
T1  - Location Choice, Product Proliferation and Entry Deterrence
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297444
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 1
SP  - 37
EP  - 45
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Within a slightly modified version of Hotelling's model we reconsider the claim that the threat of entry induces existing firms to produce a larger number of products than they would otherwise. We show that entry deterrence, although optimal, need not be achieved through product proliferation. In some cases the incumbent monopolist resorts to an entry-deterring strategy based on location choice rather than product proliferation. We also show that in some cases the number of products chosen by the incumbent facing the threat of entry is strictly greater than the minimum number required to deter entry.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297444
ER  - 



