TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dixon, Huw
T1  - Approximate Bertrand Equilibria in a Replicated Industry
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297445
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 1
SP  - 47
EP  - 62
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper considers the existence and properties of approximate Bertrand equilibria in a replicated industry. Price setting firms produce a homogeneous product with weakly convex costs. The main results are that: (a) Given ɛ &gt; 0, an ɛ-equilibrium exists if the industry is large enough; (b) If the ɛ is small enough, and the industry large enough, any ɛ-equilibrium is approximately competitive. These results depend on how contingent demand is specified.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297445
ER  - 



